content:
When you create a milestone, you must choose its recurrence type. There are three types: No Recurrence, Independent, and Sequential.

**No Recurrence**
The milestone only occurs once on the support record. The Start Date is the time when the milestone criteria are met on the record.
Example: "First Response" or "Resolution Time"

**Independent**
The milestone occurs whenever the milestone criteria match the record criteria. Only one occurrence can be active at a time.
Example: "Response Time"

**Sequential**
The milestone occurs on repeat whenever the milestone criteria match the record criteria. Only one occurrence can be active at a time.
Example: "Customer Contact Made"

When using No Recurrence, an example is a milestone named “Resolution Time” that ensures cases are resolved within 4 hours.

Independent recurrence examples include milestones like “Engineer Solution Proposed”, which tracks case escalation to Engineering and expects a proposed solution within 4 hours.

Sequential recurrence examples include milestones like “Customer Contact Made”, which tracks daily contact with a customer as part of an SLA.
title: Understanding Service Cloud Milestone Recurrence Types
